# System Workflows & User Guides

This document outlines the core workflows of the Hospital Management System (HMS) for different user roles. It explains how functionality is distributed and how users interact with the system to complete patient care cycles.

## 1. User Roles Overview

| Role | Key Responsibilities |
|------|----------------------|
| **Reception / Front Desk** | Patient Registration, Appointment Scheduling, Billing & Invoicing. |
| **Nurse** | Triage (Vitals), In-Patient Care (IPD), Ward Management. |
| **Doctor** | Consultation, Diagnosis, Prescriptions, Lab Requests, Admission Decisions. |
| **Lab Technician** | Processing Test Requests, Entering Lab Results. |
| **Admin** | User Management, Department Configuration, System Settings. |

---

## 2. OPD (Out-Patient Department) Workflow

The OPD flow handles patients who visit the hospital for consultation but do not stay overnight.

### **Flow Description:**
1.  **Registration**: New patients are registered by **Reception**. Existing patients have their records retrieved.
2.  **Appointment**: **Reception** books an appointment with a specific Doctor/Department.
3.  **Triage**: Before seeing the doctor, the **Nurse** records vital signs (BP, Temperature, Weight, etc.) in the Triage module.
4.  **Consultation**: The **Doctor** views the patient in their queue, reviews vitals, performs assessment, and records diagnosis/prescription.
5.  **Outcome**: The doctor may prescibe medicine (Pharmacy), request tests (Lab), or recommend Admission (IPD).

### **Diagram**

```mermaid
graph TD
    User((Patient)) -->|Visits Hospital| Reception
    
    subgraph Reception Module
    Reception -->|Register/Search| Pat[Patient Record]
    Pat -->|Book Slot| Appt[Appointment]
    end
    
    Appt -->|Queue| Nurse
    
    subgraph Triage Module
    Nurse -->|Record Vitals| Vitals[BP, Temp, Weight]
    end
    
    Vitals -->|Ready| Doctor
    
    subgraph Consultation Module
    Doctor -->|Review Patient| Diagnosis
    Diagnosis -->|Prescribe| Rx[Prescription]
    Diagnosis -->|Order Tests| LabReq[Lab Request]
    Diagnosis -->|Admit| AdmitDec[Admission Decision]
    end
    
    Rx -->Billing
    LabReq -->Lab
    AdmitDec -->IPD
```

